==English==

===Etymology===
Coined by [[w:Gabriel Pascal|Gabriel Pascal]] for the 1938 screenplay of [[w:George Bernard Shaw|George Bernard Shaw's]] [[w:Pygmalion (play)|Pygmalion]]. Popularised by [[w:Alan Jay Lerner|Alan Jay Lerner]] and [[w:Frederick Loewe|Frederick Loewe's]] 1956 musical adaption of the scene, [http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uVmU3iANbgk particularly this version] from the 1964 musical film "[[w:My Fair Lady|My Fair Lady]]".

